               Firſt, in that aboue all things the Lord  wiſheth vnto them the knowledge of the preſent good, and future euill, we are to obſerue, how great and fearefull is the careles ignorance of men,Obſer. and their ſupine obliuion of the time to come, by reaſon of their preſent peace and proſperitie, which Chriſt here deploreth in the Iewes, which being blinded with the peace, glory and abundance of their temporall and preſent proſperitie, neuer thought vpon the future euils, and miſeries, which for their ſinnes were ſhortly to be inflicted vpon them. For when the ſecure ſinner ſhall ſay, peace and ſafetie: then ſhall ſuddaine

