                  Repentance the ſanctuary of the ſoule.Let vs therfore (good brethrē) linger no delaies, but betime flie to repentance, the ſanctuarie of the ſoule: take heede leaſt ſinne paſſe through his gradation, and ſo get an habite. Leaſt while cuſtome groweth, man fadeth, grace abſenteth, ſin preſenteth, the heart is hardened, and man obdurate: ſo that now God is contemned, his

threatning reiected: heauen cannot winne him, nor hell ſcarre him: ioyes cannot allure him, nor torments affright him. This is Sathans ladder of perdition: ſinne ſteppeth from temptation, to thinking: from thinking, to liking: from liking, to yeelding: from yeelding, to acting: from acting to cuſtome: from cuſtome, to hardnes of heart: from hardnes of heart, to a reprobate minde, full of vnrighteouſnes, fornication, couetouſnes, enuie, murther, back-biting &amp;c. As a learned Diuine excellently obſerueth.
